 AE snaring (you can accidentally snare yourself, right?), but sometimes when you start single snaring the first two of the four mobs and you're rounding up the last two to snare, people see a &quot;walking&quot; mob and think it's unaggroed (while it's really snared and heading to me) so they attempt to engage it. I don't really fight them over it because they either figure out it's snared or I'm too far off pulling that they don't realize it's mine. And the further downside to this is that I risk losing other mobs to snare while waiting for the snared ones to catch up to me before I aggro the others. (Go off too far and your snared mob wanders around in a daze instead of pursuing you.)<br><br>Of course, I speak from my experience in Ulthorks and from the brief time I quadded in CS. I've admired the speed with which a wizard can round up four mobs (&quot;tag, it's mine&quot;) and then just snare them all at once. Wizards get their mobs faster while druids just get them a little safer.<br><br>Personally I prefer the individual snares -- I'd rather be safe than quick. I just don't like competing with other people for mobs. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.lby3.com/eq/leopa/sigs/leopard_doll.gif"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=eaminwhitefalcon>Eamin Whitefalcon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>¡Viva la inquisición!</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/1/02 2:23:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=371.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://web.tampabay.rr.com/eqsite/Eamin_small.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do you quad?</span><hr size=1> Actually, it's very difficult to snare yourself while multisnaring. I personally round them all up into a little ball, and then run off spamming my SoTF until they're out of range. I then turn around and snare. There's virtually no chance that you can possibly snare yourself using this method, unless the mobs are abnormally fast.<br>I prefer multisnaring because it uses less mana. As a Wizard, the ideal single-snaring kite will take five casts of BoF/Atol's. The ideal multi-snaring kite will take only one. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usaedyan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saedyan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/1/02 3:03:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=371.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://saedyan.freeservers.com/images/eqaddict1.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do you quad?</span><hr size=1> /nod  at Sol Ro's Servant <p><table width="50%" align="center"><tr><td align="center"><a href="http://courtofjesters.swgo.net"><img src="http://saedyan.freeservers.com/images/saedyanrobed.gif" border=0></table><table width="100%" align="center"><tr><td style="filter:glow(color=white strength=10);font-family:arial;font-weight: regular;font-size:'12pt'" align="center"><div style="width:60%; filter:progid:DXImageTransform.Microsoft.Gradient(GradientType=0,StartColorStr=FFFFFF,EndColorStr=)"><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=163816">MyProfile</a> </td></tr></div></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgco